column5: Fished Lake Nosbonsing on NYD for about an hour. Temp was -16c, and the winds were blowing accross the lake. Brother-in-law caught two perch on minnows and jig head. As we didn't have a hut, I decided once I couldn't feel my extremities that it was time to go in. Lots of huts out all over the lake.

Temps dropped pretty good for the weekend...I wonder if that had anything to do with it.  I was out in Muskoka on NYE and early NYD while it was still only -7.  Mind you...I didn't do much better than a couple perch   So there goes my "musta been the weather" excuse!
